<br>
I was in Thurg last night and was able to pick up an Etched Velium War Lance for 2k. For those of you who wonder, this is a 30/35 weapon from Dragon Necropolis. It is a very nice and pre Velious would have been top in the game. The DPS ratio on it is better than an ebon mace, before you even get to the damage bonus. It is an amazing weapon.<br>
<br>
However as I've been thinking about it, it really pointedly shows the position that casters are in. We have no way to improve ourselves this much by simply spending a couple of grand on a new weapon.<br>
<br>
Anyway, hopefully they will balance casters soon, although I've found myself much happier since I've been much less one character dependant. If I ever get frustrated with what I feel are the unequities of being a mage I can get out my Chanter or SK. This has made the game fun for me again. I would encourage those of you that are to the breaking point on Mage issues to consider this.<br>
<br>
Nandail Mandragoran<br>
55th Mage on Tunare<br>
<br>
Rhumba<br>
50th SK on Tunare<br>
<br>
Archy<br>
51st Chanter on Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 632<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/02 8:13:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: More proof of Mudflation</span><hr size=1> Part of the reason for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Melee versus Caster Item Imbalance</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is the simplicity of evaluating weapons and armor, and the ease of invent new and better ones.<br>
<br>
The situation is far less clear for casters.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Flowing Thought</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is their first attempt at simple redress, but has been demonstrated this is at best a beginning.<br>
<br>
I suspect that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>fears</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> doing the obvious, which is including items that the analogs of melee items, i.e. increase our damage output by the most direct means.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> may be apprehensive that if they significantly increase the damage throughput of casters, that things will return the imbalance pre-[/i]Kunark[/i], when melee lagged behind casters in general, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in particular.<br>
<br>
So what item effects might be analogous to melee weapon damage/delay/bonus/effects?<br>
<br>
haste, delay =&gt; Reduced Cast Time, Refresh time<br>
damage =&gt; Increased Damaged<br>
bonus =&gt; Reduced Resists<br>
regeneraton =&gt; Flowing Thought<br>
procs =&gt; right clicks<br>
<br>
There are other mechanisms of dubious import, but these seem to me to be the most direct.  I believe <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is reluctant to open the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pandora's Box</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> by introducing them into the game.  Once introduced, they would be difficult to recall, and would themselves plant the seeds of the next round of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mudflation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Personally, I would like to see an effort at adjusting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Melee versus Caster</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> balance <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>without</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> items <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>first</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<br>
