<br>
Most casters are almost as effective completely naked as we are fully geared, mages being one of the few exceptions. It's a big advantage and we shouldn't discount it, especially for those of us  who play on a PvP server. Additionally, this is really a game about acquiring stuff, and even a lot of uber caster gear just boils down to more mana and resists, frankly I don't care that much. I would be MUCH more excited to see gear that did stuff.  Right clicks, meditation bonuses, a little more oomph to our nukes.  It wouldn't really be fair for us the ask for more power without taking some of the disadvantages of gear dependancy as well. As these things got more common it would help young casters compete with all the lowbie tanks in great gear. Sometimes I'm happy that I don't have to chase decent gear like other classes, but sometimes I feel left out on the excitement of getting something shiny and new that will really help my char. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uutaelr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utaelr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#333333>(1/27/02 6:34:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: More proof of Mudflation</span><hr size=1> I agree about wanting gear that was right click.  Sad to think that one of the most wanted items in the game for mages drops off a chump like Veklator (yes i know hes not THAT easy but im comparing him to the uber mobs like Vulak) Given the toss up between getting the Robe of Darkness and the Boots of Bladecalling (only EVER being able to get either or) the boots are in my opinion more useful to us.